At least four people were wounded in a shooting in the southern city of Malmo on Monday evening, Swedish police said. According to local media, the attack took place in the downtown Drottninggatan area. One witness told the Aftonbladet newspaper that he heard 15-20 shots near a local internet cafe. Police have urged the public to remain calm. They added that they have established a perimeter in Drottninggatan. More to follow....